The paper deals with the optimization of a logistics problem involving unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and trucks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithms involve local search and a Greedy Randomized Adaptive Search Procedure (GRASP), which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem formulation and solution approach also involve mathematical optimization and algorithm design, which are relevant to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY).
